alerts.title: Winter Weather Advisory
regions: Boulder And Jefferson Counties Below 6000 Feet/West Broomfield County
North Douglas County Below 6000 Feet/Denver/West Adams and Arapahoe Counties/East Broomfield County
alerts.description: ...SNOW TODAY AND MUCH COLDER... Widespread light snow will continue across the northern Colorado mountains and northeast plains today and into this evening. In the mountains and over the Plamer Divide, storm total snowfall will range from 3 to 7 inches. Roads may become snow covered with some minor drifting snow. Across the plains, primarily north and east of Denver, snowfall is expected to be 1 to 3 inches. Temperatures will be staying cold through the rest of this afternoon with even colder readings expected overnight. As the mercury drops below zero and North winds winds continue at 15 to 25 MPH early this evening, hazardous wind chills are expected across the northeast Colorado plains. ...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM MST THIS AFTERNOON... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 5 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 8 AM MST TUESDAY... * WHAT...Snow today. Very cold wind chills expected tonight. Additional snow accumulations of up to two inches. Wind chills 10 to 20 below zero expected. * WHERE...Denver, Boulder and the western suburbs of Denver. * WHEN...Through 8 AM MST Tuesday. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous conditions could impact the morning or evening commute.
